Several airplane tragedies from August 1987 through March 1991 resulted in a high death toll; notably, 154 aboard a jetliner in Detroit; 5 aboard a small plan near Albuquerque; all 259 aboard plus 22 on the ground after a jetliner explosion over Scotland; 123 of 293 passengers on a jetliner attempting an emergency landing at an Iowa airport; 16, including a US Representative, in a small plane crash over Ethiopia; a Congressman in a light plane crash in Mississippi; 171 aboard a jetliner which exploded high over a Niger desert; and 25 in a jetliner crash near Colorado Springs, CO.